latestIgtvVideos.caption:
There are things happening all around us and we aren't even aware of them. And this was one of them for me. I had no idea so many kids across Canada are going through food insecurities which would obviously lead to poor health conditions. Thank you Chloe from @breakfastclubcanada for this informative video. Thank you Janic for being in touch with me and being so kind and supportive. @missworldcnd @missontarioworld 
.
.
It's the 2nd #COVID19 lockdown and we are all back inside. This is a tough time for many of us but we can all get through it together. 
.
.
Miss Brampton World 2020 Walks Across Canada 2020 - I thought of doing this fundraiser event because I wanted to be able to help. Not only others but myself also. Not everyday is a sunny day but I am slowly learning to accept the grey days. I hope you are able to openly reach out for help and also help others that are less fortunate that you. This Christmas season, I would like us as a community, as a country, to help organizations like BCC encouraging campaigns like "#stopchildhunger" and much more. 
.
.
You can help today! 100% of the proceeds will be going towards these charities and shelters. You can either match every KM that I walked, such as $2/km or $5/km and I walked for 20 KM. Or you can donate whatever your heart desires! Every little bit makes a difference. If you want a receipt for your taxes, donations must be over $25.

latestIgtvVideos.title: How Yoga can help improve Mental Health
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I reached out to my friend Madhuri from @bendsoyoudontbreak and asked her to be a part of my fundraiser campaign. I couldn't think of a better person to ask if she can help shed some light on how yoga helps overcome chronic mind problems. 
.
The Vagus Nerve is essentially the Queen of the parasympathetic nervous system -- a.k.a. the "rest and digest", or the "chill out" one -- so the more we do things that "stimulate" or activate it, like deep breathing, the more we banish the effects of the sympathetic nervous system -- a.k.a. the "fight or flight" or the "do something!" stress-releasing adrenaline/cortisol one. 
. 
Make sure to check out my friend as she has so much to share with all of us! Thank you Madhuri for making this lovely educational video helping us all.
.
.
@missworldcnd 
.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: My Walk Across Brampton
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I would like to thank everyone for joining my live and making my fundraiser event a success. I did this walk to raise awareness towards mental health by bringing together several professionals that gave us more information and resources. I would like to thank Dr. Maldeniya, who joined me live on Sunday, October 25, 2020. He spoke to us about the social changes around drug addictions and mental health. He especially touched upon #covid_19 and the effects it's taken on humanity. I am so thankful that we have people like Dr. Maldeniya and many other #frontlineworkers who are working hard every single day to keep essential services running. 🙏🙌
.
.
We #all need to work #together to #flattenthecurve and #protect our frontline workers. 🤍
.
.
Remember, this is a fundraising event to help the entire community, in fact, just help people in general, to network, learn, teach, and support themselves and others around them with their mental healths. latestIgtvVideos.title: How we can Stop Child Hunger in Canada
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I am honoured to be an ambassador for @breakfastclubcanada for their stop child hunger campaign. Did you know that because of #covid_19 One in three children will go to school on an empty stomach. Household food insecurity is strongly linked to school performance issues and is a risk factor for developing eating disorders and mental health conditions. 
.
.
We can all make a difference TOGETHER. 
.
.
@missworldcnd 
.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: How doing stretches can improve posture
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I reached out to my physiotherapist, Saloni Motiwala who works with Holistic Home Care. Due to #covid_19 we are all trapped at home, everyone is either doing online school or working from home which is affecting people's posture. That's why I thought we can all benefit from some tips! 
.
.
They work with patients in and around the GTA area to provide treatment and management options for those living with persistent pain and discomfort. 
.
.
As an ex-gymnast, she has a great understanding of injuries related to sports and Orthopedics. She is very caring towards her patients (personal experience). The improvement to the quality of life that is affected by injuries is a constant ongoing process with every treatment she gives. 
.
.
For more details, please e-mail: info@holistichomecare.ca or you can call (647)-830-5541 Thank you Saloni for making this video helping us all with our postures! 
.
.
@missworldcnd 
.
.
